 <item> <title>North Carolina to Receive $14.3 Million to Turn Around its Lowest-Performing Schools</title>
 <link>https://www.ed.gov/news/press-releases/north-carolina-receive-143-million-turn-around-its-lowest-performing-schools</link>
 <description>Today, U.S. Secretary of Education Arne Duncan announced that North Carolina will receive $14.3 million to turn around its persistently lowest achieving schools through the Department&#039;s School Improvement Grant (SIG) program. North Carolina is one of 13 states that will receive SIG funding.</description>
