 <item> <title>Assistant Deputy Secretary Kevin Jennings to Visit North Carolina to Meet with American Indian Students, Parents, Education Officials, Tribal Leaders</title>
 <link>https://www.ed.gov/news/media-advisories/assistant-deputy-secretary-kevin-jennings-visit-north-carolina-meet-american-indian-students-parents-education-officials-tribal-leaders</link>
 <description>Kevin Jennings, assistant deputy secretary of the U.S. Department of Education&#039;s Office of Safe and Drug-Free Schools, will visit North Carolina Tuesday and Wednesday, Nov. 30-Dec. 1, to meet with American Indian students, parents, education officials and tribal leaders. They will discuss education challenges facing American Indian students—from a rural to an urban perspective.</description>
