 <item> <title>North Carolina to Receive $14.24 Million to Turn Around Its Persistently Lowest-Achieving Schools</title>
 <link>https://www.ed.gov/news/press-releases/north-carolina-receive-1424-million-turn-around-its-persistently-lowest-achieving-schools</link>
 <description>U.S. Secretary of Education Arne Duncan today announced that North Carolina will receive $14.24 million to turn around its persistently lowest achieving schools through the School Improvement Grants (SIG) program. The funds are part of $546 million available to states for the School Improvement Grant program in fiscal year 2010.</description>
